# missing values imputation by interpolate 
Healthy_2=Healthy_1.sort_values(by="Total_Annual_Spend")
Healthy_2['Age Group']=Healthy_2['Age Group'].str.strip()
Healthy_2['Age Group'].replace('NA', np.nan, inplace = True)
Healthy_2['Income Group']=Healthy_2['Income Group'].str.strip()
Healthy_2['Income Group'].replace('NA', np.nan, inplace = True)

aa=Healthy_2['Age Group']

#classify high-opportunity vs low-opportunity customers 
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
inertias = []
ks = range(1,10)
for k in ks:
    X = scaler.fit_transform(Healthy_3_1)
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(X)
    inertias.append(model.inertia_)
#plot k vs inertia
plt.plot(ks,inertias, '-o')
plt.xlabel("number of clusters")
plt.ylabel("inertias")
plt.xticks(ks)
plt.show()

In [127]:
#n_clusters=4
km = KMeans(n_clusters=4, max_iter=100)
km.fit(X_std)
centroids = km.cluster_centers_
centroids = pd.DataFrame(centroids)
# Plot the clustered data
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
plt.scatter(X_std[km.labels_ == 0, 0], X_std[km.labels_ == 0, 1],
            c='green', label='cluster 0')
plt.scatter(X_std[km.labels_ == 1, 0], X_std[km.labels_ == 1, 1],
            c='blue', label='cluster 1')
plt.scatter(X_std[km.labels_ == 2, 0], X_std[km.labels_ == 2, 1],
            c='yellow', label='cluster 2')
plt.scatter(X_std[km.labels_ == 3, 0], X_std[km.labels_ == 3, 1],
            c='hotpink', label='cluster 3')

plt.scatter(centroids.values[:, 0], centroids.values[:, 1], marker='*', s=300,
            c='r', label='centroid')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Visualization of Clustered Data', fontweight='bold')
plt.show()
